Then by the Angle Bisector Theorem,
\[\frac{BI}{CI} = \frac{AB}{AC} = 1,\]so $CI = 8.$

By the Law of Cosines on triangle $BIC,$
\begin{align*}
a^2 &= BI^2 + CI^2 - 2 \cdot BI \cdot CI \cdot \cos BIC \\
&= 8^2 + 8^2 - 2 \cdot 8 \cdot 8 \cdot \cos \frac{A}{2} \\
