Then $TD = \sqrt{TM^2 - DM^2} = 3 \sqrt{7},$ so the distance from $T$ to face $ABC$ is $TD = \boxed{3 \sqrt{7}}.$

Solution:
Let $D$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $T$ to face $ABC.$  Let $\theta = \angle ATB.$

[asy]
import three;

size(180);
currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple A, B, C, T, D;

A = (0,0,1);
B = (1,0,1);
C = (1,1,1);
T = (0,0,0);
D = (0,0,1);

draw(surface(A--B--C--cycle),paleyellow,nolight);
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(T--A);
draw(T--B);
draw(T--C);
draw(T--D);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, dir(0));
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$T$", T, S);
label("$D$", D, N);
label("$6$", (T + C)/2, SW);
label("$12$", (T + A)/2, W);
label("$12$", (T + B)/2, E);
[/asy]

Then $\triangle ATB$ is an isosceles right triangle, so $\theta = 45^\circ.$  Then $\triangle TCD$ is a $30^\circ$-$60^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, so $TD = 6/\sqrt{3} = 2 \sqrt{3}.$  Hence, the distance from $T$ to face $ABC$ is $TD \cos \theta = 2 \sqrt{3} \cos 45^\circ = \boxed{\sqrt{6}}.$
